00:00:22.150 --> 00:00:22.830
Let's start.

00:00:22.830 --> 00:00:29.690
So last lecture we started
on the topic of doing

00:00:29.690 --> 00:00:32.304
renormalization
in position space.

00:00:35.580 --> 00:00:40.550
And the idea, let's say,
was to look at something

00:00:40.550 --> 00:00:49.110
like the Ising model, whose
partition function is obtained,

00:00:49.110 --> 00:00:53.560
if you have insides, by
summing over all the 2 to the n

00:00:53.560 --> 00:01:02.470
configuration of a weight
that tends to align variables,

00:01:02.470 --> 00:01:05.780
binary variables that
are next to each other.

00:01:05.780 --> 00:01:08.130
And this next to each
other is indicated

00:01:08.130 --> 00:01:13.500
by this nearest neighbor
symbol, sigma i, sigma j.

00:01:13.500 --> 00:01:16.820
Potentially, we may want
to add the magnetic field

00:01:16.820 --> 00:01:18.590
like term that [INAUDIBLE].

00:01:26.340 --> 00:01:31.870
The idea of the
renormalization group

00:01:31.870 --> 00:01:34.960
is to obtain a similar
Hamiltonian that

00:01:34.960 --> 00:01:41.010
describes interactions among
spins that are further apart.

00:01:41.010 --> 00:01:43.340
We saw that we
could do this easily

00:01:43.340 --> 00:01:46.200
in the case of the
one-dimensional system.

00:01:46.200 --> 00:01:54.290
Well, let's say you have a line,
and you have sites on the line.

00:01:54.290 --> 00:01:57.280
Each one of them wants to
make their neighbor parallel

00:01:57.280 --> 00:01:58.930
to itself.

00:01:58.930 --> 00:02:02.430
And what we saw was
that I could easily

00:02:02.430 --> 00:02:12.840
get rid of every other spin
and keep one set of spins.

00:02:12.840 --> 00:02:17.410
If I do it that, I get
a partition function

00:02:17.410 --> 00:02:20.720
that operates between
the remaining spins.

00:02:20.720 --> 00:02:26.350
Was very easy to sum over the
two variables that spin in

00:02:26.350 --> 00:02:29.550
between these two
could have and conclude

00:02:29.550 --> 00:02:34.340
that after this step, which
corresponds to removing half

00:02:34.340 --> 00:02:39.310
of the degrees of freedom, I
get a new interaction, k prime,

00:02:39.310 --> 00:02:47.230
which was 1/2 log hyperbolic
cosine of 2K, if h was zero.

00:02:52.690 --> 00:02:57.190
And we saw that
that, which is also

00:02:57.190 --> 00:03:01.170
a prototype of other
systems in one dimension,

00:03:01.170 --> 00:03:06.940
basically is incapable of giving
you long-range order or phase

00:03:06.940 --> 00:03:12.570
transition at finite temperature
that corresponds to finite k.

00:03:12.570 --> 00:03:18.350
So the only place where you
could have potentially ordering

00:03:18.350 --> 00:03:21.420
over large landscape
is when k becomes

00:03:21.420 --> 00:03:23.910
very large at zero temperature.

00:03:23.910 --> 00:03:27.110
We saw how the correlation
length behaves and diverges

00:03:27.110 --> 00:03:29.620
as you approach zero temperature
in this type of model.

00:03:33.040 --> 00:03:35.170
Now, the next step
would be to look

00:03:35.170 --> 00:03:37.780
at something that
is two-dimensional.

00:03:37.780 --> 00:03:45.070
And in this context,
I describe how

00:03:45.070 --> 00:03:49.460
it would be ideal if, let's say,
we start with a square lattice.

00:03:49.460 --> 00:03:53.370
We have interactions
k between neighbors.

00:03:53.370 --> 00:03:56.770
And we could potentially
do the same thing.

00:03:56.770 --> 00:04:03.980
Let's say remove one
sublattice of spins,

00:04:03.980 --> 00:04:09.110
getting interactions among the
other sublattice of spins that

00:04:09.110 --> 00:04:12.040
would again
correspond to removing

00:04:12.040 --> 00:04:14.640
half of the spins in the system.

00:04:14.640 --> 00:04:16.599
But in terms of
length scale change,

00:04:16.599 --> 00:04:19.700
it corresponds to
square root of 2.

00:04:19.700 --> 00:04:22.580
This length compared
to the old length

00:04:22.580 --> 00:04:27.560
is different by a factor
of square root of 2.

00:04:27.560 --> 00:04:30.500
But the thing that
I also indicated

00:04:30.500 --> 00:04:34.490
was that this spin is now
coupled to all four of them.

00:04:34.490 --> 00:04:38.850
And once I remove the spin, I
can generate new interactions

00:04:38.850 --> 00:04:42.030
operating between these spins.

00:04:42.030 --> 00:04:45.630
In fact, you will generate
also a four-spin interaction,

00:04:45.630 --> 00:04:48.380
so your space of
parameters is not

00:04:48.380 --> 00:04:51.660
closed under this procedure.

00:04:51.660 --> 00:04:57.810
The same applies to all
higher dimensional systems,

00:04:57.810 --> 00:05:01.680
and so they are not really
solvable by this approach

00:05:01.680 --> 00:05:05.470
unless you start making
some approximations.

00:05:05.470 --> 00:05:09.010
So the particular approximation
that I introduced here

00:05:09.010 --> 00:05:13.750
was done and applied shortly
after Cavenaugh brought forth

00:05:13.750 --> 00:05:18.210
this idea of removing degrees
of freedom and renormalization

00:05:18.210 --> 00:05:22.830
by-- I'll write this
once, and hopefully I

00:05:22.830 --> 00:05:24.350
will not make a mistake.

00:05:28.600 --> 00:05:37.440
Niemeijer and van
Leeuwen And it's

00:05:37.440 --> 00:05:44.750
a kind of cumulant expansion,
as I will describe shortly.

00:05:44.750 --> 00:05:45.756
It's an approximation.

00:05:48.540 --> 00:05:52.185
And rather than doing
the square lattice,

00:05:52.185 --> 00:05:55.960
it is applied to the
triangular lattice.

00:05:55.960 --> 00:05:57.550
And that's going
to be the hardest

00:05:57.550 --> 00:06:00.812
part of this class for me,
to draw a triangular lattice.

00:06:19.895 --> 00:06:21.170
Not doing a good job.

00:06:39.750 --> 00:06:47.530
So basically, we put our
spins, sigma i plus minus 1,

00:06:47.530 --> 00:06:50.020
on the sides of this.

00:06:50.020 --> 00:06:55.080
And we put an interaction k
that operates between neighbors.

00:06:55.080 --> 00:06:59.330
And we want to do a
renormalization in which we

00:06:59.330 --> 00:07:02.920
reduce the number of
degrees of freedom.

00:07:02.920 --> 00:07:08.220
What Niemeijer and van Leeuwen
suggested was the following.

00:07:08.220 --> 00:07:15.020
You can group the
sublattices of the triangular

00:07:15.020 --> 00:07:17.640
lattice into three.

00:07:17.640 --> 00:07:21.590
I have indicated
them by 1, 2, 3.

00:07:21.590 --> 00:07:32.250
Basically, there is going
to be some selection

00:07:32.250 --> 00:07:37.340
of sublattice sites
on this lattice.

00:07:37.340 --> 00:07:42.490
What they suggested was to
basically define cells--

00:07:42.490 --> 00:07:45.750
so this would be one cell.

00:07:45.750 --> 00:07:48.635
This would be another cell.

00:07:51.500 --> 00:07:53.185
This would be another cell.

00:07:56.030 --> 00:07:59.710
This would be another
cell over here-- such

00:07:59.710 --> 00:08:05.260
that every side of the
original lattice belongs to one

00:08:05.260 --> 00:08:18.840
and only one site
of these cells.

00:08:18.840 --> 00:08:19.340
OK.

00:08:19.340 --> 00:08:25.030
So basically, I guess the
next one would come over here.

00:08:25.030 --> 00:08:27.250
All right.

00:08:27.250 --> 00:08:36.559
So let's call the
site by label i.

00:08:36.559 --> 00:08:45.270
And let's give the cells label
that I will indicate by Greek.

00:08:45.270 --> 00:08:48.480
So sites, I will
indicate i, j, cells,

00:08:48.480 --> 00:08:52.980
by Greek letters,
alphabet, et cetera.

00:08:52.980 --> 00:08:55.910
So that, for example,
we can regard

00:08:55.910 --> 00:09:02.410
this as cell alpha,
this one, this triangle,

00:09:02.410 --> 00:09:03.690
as forming cell beta.

00:09:15.200 --> 00:09:18.750
Now, the idea of
Niemeijer and van Leeuwen

00:09:18.750 --> 00:09:23.520
was that to each
cell, we are going

00:09:23.520 --> 00:09:29.850
to assign a new spin that is
reflective of the configuration

00:09:29.850 --> 00:09:32.860
of the site spins.

00:09:32.860 --> 00:09:36.690
So for this, they propose
the majority rule.

00:09:39.610 --> 00:09:45.250
Basically, they said that
we call the spin for site

00:09:45.250 --> 00:09:51.920
alpha to be the majority
of the site spins.

00:10:04.550 --> 00:10:09.580
So basically, if all three
spins are plus or all three

00:10:09.580 --> 00:10:14.160
of them are minus, you
basically go to plus or minus.

00:10:14.160 --> 00:10:17.030
If two of them are plus
and one of them is minus,

00:10:17.030 --> 00:10:19.910
you would choose the
one that is a majority.

00:10:19.910 --> 00:10:24.440
So you can see that this also
has only two possibilities,

00:10:24.440 --> 00:10:28.210
plus 1 and minus 1, which
would not have taken place

00:10:28.210 --> 00:10:30.645
if I had tried to do a
majority of two sites.

00:10:30.645 --> 00:10:32.350
It would have worked
if I had chosen

00:10:32.350 --> 00:10:35.210
a majority of three sites
on a one-dimensional lattice

00:10:35.210 --> 00:10:36.890
clearly.

00:10:36.890 --> 00:10:39.540
So that's the rule.

00:10:39.540 --> 00:10:43.110
So you can see that for every
configuration that I have

00:10:43.110 --> 00:10:46.670
originally, I can do
these kinds of averaging

00:10:46.670 --> 00:10:51.790
and define a configuration
that exists for the cells.

00:10:51.790 --> 00:10:57.170
And the idea is that if I weigh
the initial configurations

00:10:57.170 --> 00:10:59.320
according to the weight
where the nearest neighbor

00:10:59.320 --> 00:11:03.030
coupling is k, what is
the weight that governs

00:11:03.030 --> 00:11:09.350
these new configurations for
the averaged or majority cell

00:11:09.350 --> 00:11:09.850
spins?

00:11:12.430 --> 00:11:16.240
Now, to do this
problem exactly is

00:11:16.240 --> 00:11:19.900
subject to the same difficulty
that I mentioned before.

00:11:19.900 --> 00:11:22.810
That is, if I somehow
do an averaging

00:11:22.810 --> 00:11:26.390
over the spins in here
to get the majority,

00:11:26.390 --> 00:11:28.780
then I will generate
interactions

00:11:28.780 --> 00:11:31.820
that run over further
neighboring, as we

00:11:31.820 --> 00:11:34.060
will see shortly.

00:11:34.060 --> 00:11:38.850
So to remove that,
they introduced a kind

00:11:38.850 --> 00:11:44.410
of uncontrolled break-up
of the Hamiltonian

00:11:44.410 --> 00:11:45.670
that governed the system.

00:11:45.670 --> 00:11:49.220
That is, they wrote
beta H minus beta

00:11:49.220 --> 00:11:58.020
H, which is the sum over
all neighboring site spins,

00:11:58.020 --> 00:12:04.940
as the sum of a part that
then cancels perturbatively

00:12:04.940 --> 00:12:10.240
and a part of that will treat
as a correction to the part

00:12:10.240 --> 00:12:13.100
that we can solve exactly.

00:12:13.100 --> 00:12:28.300
The beta H zero is this
sum over all cells alpha.

00:12:28.300 --> 00:12:30.460
What you do is
basically you just

00:12:30.460 --> 00:12:33.590
include the interactions
among the cell spins.

00:12:33.590 --> 00:12:42.620
So I have K sigma alpha 1
sigma alpha 2 sigma alpha

00:12:42.620 --> 00:12:49.020
2 sigma alpha 3 sigma
alpha 3 sigma alpha 1.

00:12:49.020 --> 00:12:53.700
So basically, these are the
interactions within a cell.

00:12:53.700 --> 00:12:54.960
What have I left out?

00:12:54.960 --> 00:12:59.245
I have left out the interactions
that operate between cells,

00:12:59.245 --> 00:13:02.260
so all of these things,
which, of course, are

00:13:02.260 --> 00:13:08.680
the same strength but, for
lack of better things to do,

00:13:08.680 --> 00:13:09.720
they said OK.

00:13:09.720 --> 00:13:14.060
We are going to sum over
all, you can see now,

00:13:14.060 --> 00:13:16.020
neighboring cells.

00:13:16.020 --> 00:13:18.215
So the things that
I left out, let's

00:13:18.215 --> 00:13:22.720
say, interactions between
this cell alpha and beta,

00:13:22.720 --> 00:13:27.180
evolve-- let's say
the spin number

00:13:27.180 --> 00:13:35.920
1 in this labeling of beta
times spin number 2 of alpha

00:13:35.920 --> 00:13:39.180
and spin number 3 of alpha.

00:13:39.180 --> 00:13:42.550
Now, of course, what
I call 1, 2, or 3

00:13:42.550 --> 00:13:47.190
will depend on the relative
orientation of the neighboring

00:13:47.190 --> 00:13:47.690
cells.

00:13:47.690 --> 00:13:49.640
But the idea is the
same, that basically,

00:13:49.640 --> 00:13:51.850
for each pair of
neighboring cells,

00:13:51.850 --> 00:13:55.870
there will be two of
these interactions.

00:13:55.870 --> 00:14:00.030
So again, these no a
priori reason to regard

00:14:00.030 --> 00:14:02.380
this as a perturbation.

00:14:02.380 --> 00:14:06.010
Both of them clearly carry the
same strength for the bond,

00:14:06.010 --> 00:14:09.840
this parameter K. OK?

00:14:09.840 --> 00:14:14.620
The justification
is only solvability.

00:14:14.620 --> 00:14:19.690
So the partition function
that I have to calculate,

00:14:19.690 --> 00:14:26.440
which is the sum of
all spin configuration

00:14:26.440 --> 00:14:34.270
with the original weight, I can
write as a sum over all spin

00:14:34.270 --> 00:14:42.810
configurations of e to the minus
beta H 0, and then minus u,

00:14:42.810 --> 00:14:44.710
and the idea of
perturbation is, of course,

00:14:44.710 --> 00:14:48.490
to write the part that depends
on u as a perturbation.

00:14:52.560 --> 00:14:54.220
It's expanding the exponential.

00:14:59.040 --> 00:15:02.650
Now, solvability
relies on the fact

00:15:02.650 --> 00:15:06.750
that the term that
just multiplies 1

00:15:06.750 --> 00:15:10.260
is the sum of
triplets that are only

00:15:10.260 --> 00:15:12.690
interacting between themselves.

00:15:12.690 --> 00:15:13.900
They don't see anybody else.

00:15:13.900 --> 00:15:16.690
So that's clearly
very easily solvable,

00:15:16.690 --> 00:15:19.880
and we can calculate
the partition functions

00:15:19.880 --> 00:15:22.636
0 that describes that.

00:15:26.270 --> 00:15:29.840
And then we can
start to evaluate

00:15:29.840 --> 00:15:33.870
all of those other terms,
once I have pulled out

00:15:33.870 --> 00:15:38.590
e to the minus beta H zero sum
over all configurations in Z 0.

00:15:38.590 --> 00:15:41.050
The series that I
will generate are

00:15:41.050 --> 00:15:44.750
averages of this
interaction calculated

00:15:44.750 --> 00:15:47.129
with the 0 [INAUDIBLE]
Hamiltonian.

00:15:52.120 --> 00:16:06.140
So my log of Z-- OK.

00:16:06.140 --> 00:16:11.090
That's how if I was to calculate
the problem perturbatively.

00:16:11.090 --> 00:16:15.990
Now I'm going to do something
that is slightly different.

00:16:15.990 --> 00:16:19.930
So what I will do
is, rather than

00:16:19.930 --> 00:16:23.180
do the sum that I
have indicated above,

00:16:23.180 --> 00:16:24.755
I will do a slight variation.

00:16:29.350 --> 00:16:35.990
I will sum only
over configurations.

00:16:35.990 --> 00:16:38.060
Maybe I should write
it in this fashion.

00:16:38.060 --> 00:16:41.660
I will sum only
over configurations

00:16:41.660 --> 00:16:48.940
that under averaging give me
a particular configuration

00:16:48.940 --> 00:16:52.630
of site spins.

00:16:52.630 --> 00:16:57.670
So, basically, let's say I pick
a configuration in which this

00:16:57.670 --> 00:17:01.030
is-- the cell spin is plus,
the cell spin is minus,

00:17:01.030 --> 00:17:05.349
whatever, some
configuration of cell spins.

00:17:05.349 --> 00:17:07.950
Now, depending on this
cell spin being plus,

00:17:07.950 --> 00:17:10.160
there are many
configurations-- not many--

00:17:10.160 --> 00:17:13.290
but there are four
configurations of the site

00:17:13.290 --> 00:17:16.250
spins that would correspond
to this being plus.

00:17:16.250 --> 00:17:19.480
There are four configurations
that would correspond to this.

00:17:19.480 --> 00:17:27.260
So basically, I specify
what configuration of cell

00:17:27.260 --> 00:17:30.710
spins I want, and I do this sum.

00:17:30.710 --> 00:17:34.930
So the answer there is
some kind of a weight that

00:17:34.930 --> 00:17:37.380
depends on my choice
of [INAUDIBLE] sigma

00:17:37.380 --> 00:17:39.680
alpha [INAUDIBLE].

00:17:39.680 --> 00:17:42.000
OK.

00:17:42.000 --> 00:17:44.240
So then I have the
same thing over here.

00:17:51.740 --> 00:17:56.510
And then, in principle,
all of these quantities

00:17:56.510 --> 00:18:02.000
will become a function of the
choice of my configuration.

00:18:08.190 --> 00:18:10.980
OK.

00:18:10.980 --> 00:18:17.180
So this is a weight
for cell configurations

00:18:17.180 --> 00:18:21.030
once I average out over all
site configurations that

00:18:21.030 --> 00:18:23.350
are compatible with that.

00:18:23.350 --> 00:18:30.520
So if I take the
log of this, I can

00:18:30.520 --> 00:18:39.190
think of that as an
effective Hamiltonian that

00:18:39.190 --> 00:18:43.880
operates on these variables.

00:18:43.880 --> 00:18:46.930
And this is what we
have usually been

00:18:46.930 --> 00:18:49.715
indicating by the
prime interactions.

00:18:55.300 --> 00:18:59.605
And so, if I take the
log of that expression,

00:18:59.605 --> 00:19:03.730
I will get log of z 0 that
is compatible with the choice

00:19:03.730 --> 00:19:09.770
of cell spins.

00:19:09.770 --> 00:19:12.480
And then the log
of this series--

00:19:12.480 --> 00:19:17.700
we've seen this many times--
it starts with minus U 0

00:19:17.700 --> 00:19:20.800
as a function of the
specified interactions.

00:19:20.800 --> 00:19:28.870
And then I have
the variance, again

00:19:28.870 --> 00:19:30.893
compatible with
the interactions.

00:19:35.794 --> 00:19:36.294
OK?

00:19:44.670 --> 00:19:48.880
So now it comes to basically
solving this problem.

00:19:48.880 --> 00:19:53.670
And I pick some particular cell.

00:19:53.670 --> 00:20:00.660
And I look at what
configurations

00:20:00.660 --> 00:20:04.620
I could have that
are compactible

00:20:04.620 --> 00:20:10.310
for a particular sign
of the cell spin.

00:20:10.310 --> 00:20:13.344
As far as the site
spins are concerned.

00:20:17.600 --> 00:20:21.875
And I will also
indicate what the weight

00:20:21.875 --> 00:20:29.130
is that I have to put for that
cell coming from minus beta H0.

00:20:32.820 --> 00:20:35.870
one thing that I
can certainly do

00:20:35.870 --> 00:20:40.070
is to have the cell spin plus.

00:20:40.070 --> 00:20:43.360
And I indicated that
that I can get either

00:20:43.360 --> 00:20:47.390
by having all three
spins to be plus or just

00:20:47.390 --> 00:20:50.370
the majority, which means
that one of the three

00:20:50.370 --> 00:20:51.525
can become minus.

00:20:54.410 --> 00:20:56.640
So there are these
configurations

00:20:56.640 --> 00:21:00.095
that are consistent, all
of them, with the sigma

00:21:00.095 --> 00:21:05.050
alpha prime, the
majority that is plus.

00:21:05.050 --> 00:21:09.180
And there are four
configurations

00:21:09.180 --> 00:21:12.837
that correspond to minuses we
shall obtain by essentially

00:21:12.837 --> 00:21:13.670
flipping everything.

00:21:22.530 --> 00:21:24.510
And the weights are
easy to figure out.

00:21:24.510 --> 00:21:28.660
Basically I have
a triplet of spins

00:21:28.660 --> 00:21:32.570
that are coupled by
interaction K. In this case,

00:21:32.570 --> 00:21:34.180
all three are positive.

00:21:34.180 --> 00:21:37.920
So I have three
into the K factor,

00:21:37.920 --> 00:21:41.680
so I will get e to the 3K.

